The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Sneha Biswas, a Class VII student, was injured when a concrete chunk fell on her head at Barasat railway station on Thursday. A section of passengers began a demonstration alleging that poor quality material had been used for the stations renovation. Railway police and senior station officials assured the protesters that the damaged parts would be examined.    CPM activist Sanjay Mondal, 38, was shot in his abdomen on Thursday at Baruipur allegedly by Trinamul Congress activists. Police said the assailants fired three rounds at him and one of the bullets hit him. He is undergoing treatment at MR Bangur Hospital.    Family members of Jayanta Chakraborty, 45, a Howrah resident who have been missing since Monday, lodged a missing diary with Bally police station on Thursday. Police said Jayanta, a trader, had left home around 9am on Monday.    Prabir Guha, 40, a rickshawpuller from Belur in Howrah, was struck by lightning on Thursday in front of the Belur ESR Hospital. He was taken to Howrah State General Hospital where he was declared dead on arrival.    A 78-year-old man jumped on the tracks at Esplanade Metro Railway station on Thursday morning. Passengers on the platform immediately alerted the Metro Railway staff who lifted him to safety. The man is suffering from a severe prostate problem and jumped on the tracks to relieve himself. He was unaware of the third rail that carries electricity, said police.                                                                                                                                               
